Employee Records Database Management & Analysis

This project demonstrates the use of SQL for managing and analyzing employee data using MySQL Workbench. The dataset contains employee details including personal information, department, salary, and joining date.
The objective of this project is to perform:
1.CRUD operations
2.Filtering and sorting
3.Aggregation and grouping
4.Joins
5.Views
6.Stored Procedures

Business Insights From the analysis:
1.Identified highest and lowest salary employees
2.Analyzed department-wise salary distribution
3.Determined average salary by country
4.Created reusable views for reporting
5.Automated queries using stored procedures
6.Implemented salary calculation functions
User-defined FunctionsThis project demonstrates practical implementation of SQL concepts including CRUD operations, filtering, sorting, aggregation, joins, views, stored procedures, and user-defined functions.
The project reflects real-world database management practices used in organizations for employee data management and reporting.
